    <div class="row">
      
      <div class="span5">
	<p i18n:translate="about-background-p1">
	  C3S consists of a group of people that initiated the project and a growing number of active supporters helping and counseling.
	</p>
	<p i18n:translate="about-background-p2">
	  Formally C3S is a project of OpenMusicContest.org e.V (a non-profit association) in coordination with other independent persons. You can read up on why we decided to choose this path here.
	<p>
      </div>
      
      
      <div class="span5">
	<p i18n:translate="about-background-p3">
	  Representing various stakeholders and domains, all individual team members, no matter if supporter or initiator, add their personal view complementing each other. We want to consider and integrate all intentions and skills of those people who all together can help in shaping an improved environment for independent artists. This is essential for establishing a collecting society that embraces digital society - it takes composers and writers, musicians, users, but as well it's lawyers, economists, software developers and netizens who are needed... to name but a few.
	</p>
      </div>
      
      
      <div class="span5">
	<p i18n:translate="about-background-p4">
	  We are happy to receive feedback from you and everybody. Feedback, be it positive or negative, is an important basis for a project like this: collectively form a collecting society. Most of all we need support. Everybody who wants to join us and help in whatever way can choose from a wide range of items, see <a href="/support">the support page</a>. We are looking forward to hearing from you!
	</p>
	
	<p i18n:translate="about-background-p5">
	  No matter who the members of the *construction team* are: When C3S has been founded, according to the statutes only musicians (performers) and composers and writers respectively (creators) can become members of C3S. Supporters of C3S can join a supporting association or be elected into the advisory board of C3S.
	</p>
      </div>

